Peptide Data Template

May 10, 2021

Upload Data

Expression Data

An unlabelled peptide expression data file called pep_edata.csv was uploaded to pmart. The column that designates unique molecules was marked as Mass_Tag_ID. The original scale of the data was raw intensity and was transformed to log2. The value to denote missing data was NA and the expression data was not normalized.

Biomolecule Information

An associated biomolecule information file was also uploaded called pep_emeta.csv and the protein identifier column was designated as Protein.

Group Samples

Sample Information

An associated sample information file was also uploaded called pep_fdata.csv. This metadata file does contain peptide to protein mappings. Trimmed sample names were not used. The column in the sample information file which indicates sample names was designated as SampleID.

Filter

Filters were applied.

Summary of Applied Filters

Filter Type Applied Parameters
Molecule Filter Biomolecule Yes Molecule Number Min: 2
CV Filter Biomolecule Yes Max CV: 150
imd-ANOVA Filter Biomolecule Yes ANOVA Min: 2 & G-test Min: 3
Proteomics Filter Biomolecule Yes Peptide Number Min: 2 & Remove Degenerates: Yes
rMD Filter Sample Yes P-Value Threshold: 0.001 & Outlier Metrics: MAD, Kurtosis, Skewness, Correlation
Custom Filter Sample Yes Samples with Infection5 were removed.

Molecule Filter

A molecule filter was applied. This means that 1814 biomolecules were filtered at a minimum of 2 observations of a unique biomolecule per sample.

Count Before Filter Number Filtered Remaining
17407 1814 15593

CV Filter

A CV filter was applied. This means that 3 biomolecules were filtered, since their coefficient of variation was greater than 150. For each biomolecule, the CV of each group is calculated as the standard deviation divided by the mean, excluding missing values. A pooled CV estimate is then calculated based on the methods of Ahmed (1995).

Count Before Filter Number Filtered Remaining
15593 3 15590

Normalization

Manual

Manual normalization was used to normalize the data.

SPANS

SPANS normalization was not used to normalize the data.
